<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Bio-ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lefebvre" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[352,461,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latinus">
<emphasis box="[352,461,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. latinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a lowland and hillside species of open environments, rarely found over 
<quantity box="[1329,1403,151,176]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
of altitude (
<bibRefCitation author="Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[251,451,188,213]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" pagination="69 - 122" refId="ref16974" refString="Pantaleoni, R. A. (1990 a) I Neurotteri (Neuropteroidea) della Valle del Bidente-Ronco (Appennino Romagnolo). Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia &quot; Guido Grandi &quot; dell'Universita di Bologna, 44, 69 - 122." type="journal article" year="1990">
Pantaleoni 1990 
<bibRefCitation author="Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[438,451,188,213]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" pagination="123 - 134" refId="ref17016" refString="Pantaleoni, R. A. (1990 b) Neurotteri e fasce di vegetazione in Romagna. Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia &quot; Guido Grandi &quot; dell'Universita di Bologna, 44, 123 - 134." type="journal article" year="1990">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1990b). This ascalaphid is typical of open Mediterranean biotopes such as grasslands and scrublands. The larvae are ambush predators living on the soil surface, camouflaging themselves with detritus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="308" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis box="[199,352,260,285]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,260,285]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species is an endemism of the Apennine Peninsula, not crossing the Po river and absent from most of northern 
<collectingCountry box="[407,462,295,320]" name="Italy" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Italy</collectingCountry>
; there are some reports from neighbouring areas of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1146,1226,296,319]" name="France" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">France</collectingCountry>
. The absence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lefebvre" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. latinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Sicily is particularly noteworthy as this ascalaphid is well known for Aspromonte, the southernmost part of the peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lefebvre" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[464,569,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latinus">
<emphasis box="[464,569,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. latinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly recognizable thanks to the pigmentation pattern of the head and the characteristic dark spots on the inferior side of the dorsal series of abdominal scolus-like processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
